{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01J1CV83ULMpaVZWeHGc6vFx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cluster has no master, so we can't call the voting_config_exclusions API. I need another approach.\n\nLooking at this problem:\n- ES 7.x uses \"zen2\" discovery\n- The voting configuration is stored in `_state/nodes-0.st` (node state file) or similar files in the data directory\n- To fix this, we need to either:\n  1. Use `unsafe-bootstrap` on the node (requires running `elasticsearch-node unsafe-bootstrap` inside the container)\n  2. Modify the elasticsearch.yml configuration to include `cluster.initial_master_nodes` with a different value and restart\n  \nActually, ES 7.17 has the `elasticsearch-node unsafe-bootstrap` tool that forces a single node to form a new cluster from its existing data. Since we're in a container, I'd need to stop Elasticsearch, run the recovery tool, and restart it.\n\nThe tricky part is managing this inside a running container—I'd need to use kubectl exec to stop the service, execute the recovery command, and restart. But there's another angle: the `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting only applies during initial bootstrap, while the actual voting configuration lives in the cluster state on disk. I could patch the StatefulSet to set `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to just `es-cluster-0`, then restart that pod. Since the data is on the PVC, it should survive the restart. Let me check the current ES configuration to see what we're working with. Once the cluster state exists, `cluster.initial_master_nodes` gets ignored and the voting configuration is locked into the cluster state itself. For unsafe recovery when quorum is lost, I need to use `elasticsearch-node unsafe-bootstrap`, which stops the node and forcefully creates a new cluster state designating it as the sole master-eligible node so it can start as a single-node cluster. Let me locate the elasticsearch-node binary and run it.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1648,"cache_read_input_tokens":45139,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1648},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1e168720-12b8-4366-8556-11e63d408ae8","uuid":"2234499a-3199-40ca-a14c-eb5fb7174750","request_id":"req_011CcMVSrATYVZ5Gztgib3NY"}
