{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0194md6pxLLQv9t7or2JUL9j","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The config is in a file at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.yml`. I can see it's mounted somehow - either as a ConfigMap or it's baked into the image.\n\nLet me check if there's a ConfigMap that mounts this file.\n\nThe issue is: \n- `cluster.initial_master_nodes` has all 3 nodes\n- `discovery.seed_hosts` has all 3 nodes\n- When the cluster had its state (after initial bootstrap), the voting configuration was committed to disk with all 3 nodes as master-eligible\nI could patch the elasticsearch.yml to use `discovery.type: single-node`, which would bypass the cluster election logic and make it act as a standalone node. The key question is whether it would preserve the existing data from the data directory, which it should. First, I need to find where the elasticsearch.yml is coming from - whether it's a ConfigMap or baked into the image.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1861,"cache_read_input_tokens":48727,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1861},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1e168720-12b8-4366-8556-11e63d408ae8","uuid":"adf2f58e-66be-45dd-8eeb-d3cd01141b2a","request_id":"req_011CcMVWR4xaFdLFnCXAvopG"}
