{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01788q4WUDk2kv5MYTgDEWaE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the real error:\n\n```\njava.lang.IllegalStateException: cannot start with [discovery.type] set to [single-node] when local node {es-cluster-0}{TSQx0uwcSfKXXW12f0iqPw} does not have quorum in voting configuration VotingConfiguration{c8Nsx1mXTRqvb3E3NpYaEQ,TSQx0uwcSfKXXW12f0iqPw,zqhE1KSkRban2GTpcHm5Cg}\n```\n\nThe issue is that Elasticsearch 7.17 won't allow single-node mode when the persisted voting configuration on disk still contains all three nodes. Since `es-cluster-0` is the only node running, it can't achieve quorum. I need to use `elasticsearch-node unsafe-bootstrap` to reset the voting configuration and designate this node as the sole member of the cluster.\n\nThe tricky part is that the container keeps restarting in CrashLoopBackOff, so I can't reliably exec into it during those brief windows when it's running. Instead, I should patch the StatefulSet to add an init container that runs the unsafe-bootstrap command before Elasticsearch starts normally.\n```\necho y | /usr/share/elasticsearch/bin/elasticsearch-node unsafe-bootstrap\n```\nThis init container needs the same image and volume mounts as the main ES container so it can access the data directory. Once I apply this patch and delete the pod to trigger a recreate, the init container will run first to bootstrap the node, then the main container will start. I need to verify the exact image tag for the Elasticsearch version being used.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1457,"cache_read_input_tokens":56822,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1457},"output_tokens":69,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1e168720-12b8-4366-8556-11e63d408ae8","uuid":"b63984da-d6dc-4102-8b09-013e1ddf4fda","request_id":"req_011CcMVnugqyn3uPYEcPLrbA"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01788q4WUDk2kv5MYTgDEWaE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ES 7.17 explicitly blocks `single-node` when the persisted voting configuration includes other nodes. I must run `elasticsearch-node unsafe-bootstrap` to reset the on-disk voting config. I'll add a one-shot init container to do this."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1457,"cache_read_input_tokens":56822,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1457},"output_tokens":69,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1e168720-12b8-4366-8556-11e63d408ae8","uuid":"aa7f5420-bcc7-4620-b50c-6a790e3ecdd6","request_id":"req_011CcMVnugqyn3uPYEcPLrbA"}
