{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JSZ4UriW2cMzk5MougpQQB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to:\n1. Revert the ConfigMap to remove `discovery.type: single-node` (since it causes a crash)\n2. Add an init container to the StatefulSet that runs `elasticsearch-node unsafe-bootstrap`\n3. The init container will reset the voting configuration on disk\n4. Then the main ES container will start normally with the original discovery settings (but without nodes 1 and 2 - hmm, they're gone so they'll just be unresolvable, but ES 7.17 should still start if it was bootstrapped)\n\nWait, actually after `unsafe-bootstrap`, the voting configuration will be reset to just `es-cluster-0`. \n\nAfter the bootstrap, the node will have a voting configuration of just itself, so it can start with the original discovery settings pointing to the missing nodes—those will just generate warnings. The `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting only matters for initial bootstrapping anyway and gets ignored once there's an existing cluster state. The key is removing `discovery.type: single-node` since that's what's causing the crash.\n\nActually, rethinking this: after `unsafe-bootstrap` updates the voting config to only include `es-cluster-0`, that node will have quorum by itself, so `discovery.type: single-node` should work. But the simpler approach is to just revert the ConfigMap to the original settings without that flag and let Elasticsearch use normal discovery with the updated voting configuration from the bootstrap—with only one node in the voting config, it can elect itself as master.\n\nThe key is that `unsafe-bootstrap` modifies the voting configuration on disk, so when Elasticsearch starts normally afterward, it will try to contact the other nodes (which will fail with DNS warnings) but will successfully elect itself as master since it has quorum. I need to make sure the init container running `elasticsearch-node` has access to the same configuration paths that the main process uses, likely through environment variables or default paths that the script already knows about.\n\nFor the init container, I'll use the same Elasticsearch image, mount the data volume, set the necessary Java options, and run the unsafe-bootstrap command with a piped confirmation. Then I'll patch the StatefulSet to include this init container.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1480,"cache_read_input_tokens":58279,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1480},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1e168720-12b8-4366-8556-11e63d408ae8","uuid":"a28a68e2-2b5e-4f48-870c-fa22e99f0671","request_id":"req_011CcMVpKmxsUU5hxMrghtno"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JSZ4UriW2cMzk5MougpQQB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"First, revert the ConfigMap to remove `discovery.type: single-node` (since it blocks startup when voting config includes other nodes), then add an init container that runs `unsafe-bootstrap` to reset the on-disk voting config."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1480,"cache_read_input_tokens":58279,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1480},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1e168720-12b8-4366-8556-11e63d408ae8","uuid":"93a3a20e-4c5f-4d59-9212-6b7511780495","request_id":"req_011CcMVpKmxsUU5hxMrghtno"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JSZ4UriW2cMzk5MougpQQB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HZcUKR8FjV6ax8QYLQtf1G","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"export KC=/mydata/karma/runs/examples-rerererun/elasticsearch-safe-downscale-with-shard-migration-20260624_044408/bundle/kubeconfig\n# Revert ConfigMap to original (remove discovery.type: single-node)\nkubectl --kubeconfig=$KC patch configmap es-config -n elasticsearch --type=merge -p '{\n  \"data\": {\n    \"elasticsearch.yml\": \"cluster.name: es-cluster\\nnode.name: ${POD_NAME}\\nnode.roles: [ master, data, ingest ]\\nnetwork.host: 0.0.0.0\\ndiscovery.seed_hosts:\\n  - es-cluster-0.es-cluster\\n  - es-cluster-1.es-cluster\\n  - es-cluster-2.es-cluster\\ncluster.initial_master_nodes:\\n  - es-cluster-0\\n  - es-cluster-1\\n  - es-cluster-2\\ningest.geoip.downloader.enabled: false\\nnode.store.allow_mmap: false\\nxpack.security.enabled: false\\nxpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: false\\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: false\\n\"\n  }\n}' 2>&1","description":"Revert es-config ConfigMap to original settings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1480,"cache_read_input_tokens":58279,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1480},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1e168720-12b8-4366-8556-11e63d408ae8","uuid":"d0769017-8fcf-40aa-9bac-e192514a2389","request_id":"req_011CcMVpKmxsUU5hxMrghtno"}
